description: Revised application for approval of reserved matters: siting, design, external appearance, means of access and landscaping of initial stage (Barking Life Long Learning Centre and Garden Housing) of mixed use development for Barking Town Square (replacement of previous approval 04/00770/REM, increasing number of dwellings from 206 to 246).
decision_conditions: The proposed service area off Axe Street shall not be used for the loading and unloading of vehicles between the hours of 10.30 pm and 7.00 am.Reason:  In order to protect neighbouring residential occupiers from noise and disturbance at unsocial hours and in accordance with policy G36 of the Unitary Development Plan.
No soakaways shall be constructed in contaminated ground. Reason:  To prevent pollution of groundwater and in accordance with policy G38 of the Unitary Development Plan.

Surface water drainage works and source control measures shall be carried out in accordance with details which shall have been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority before the occupation of the development.Reason:  To prevent the increased risk of flooding and to prevent pollution of the water environment and in accordance with policies G33 and G38 of the Unitary Development Plan.

The Lifelong Learning Centre and Garden Housing shall not be occupied until a scheme showing the detailed provision made for cycle parking has been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority and the agreed scheme for that part of the development has been implemented.Reason:  In the interests of promoting cycling as a safe, efficient and non-polluting form of transport and in accordance with policy T19 of the Unitary Development Plan.

No part of the Lifelong Learning Centre and Garden Housing hereby approved shall be occupied until a plan showing details of the ramped access between Axe Street and the service yard area to include details of any retaining walls has been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority and thereafter implemented.Reason:  To ensure that the access is suitable for service and other vehicles and in accordance with policy T32 of the Unitary Development Plan.

No part of the Lifelong Learning Centre and Garden Housing hereby approved shall be occupied until details of the radar operated traffic lights in the rear service and access road have been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority and thereafter implemented.Reason:  In the interests of highway safety and in accordance with policy T32 of the Unitary Development Plan.

Details/samples of all facing materials to be used in the development shall be submitted and approved by the Local Planning Authority prior to the installation of the said facing material and no facing materials shall be used except those so approved.Reason: To safeguard the appearance of the development and in accordance with policy DE1 of the Unitary Development Plan.

No dwellings on the seventh floor shall be occupied until details of the privacy screens between the units have been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority and thereafter implemented.Reason:  To protect the privacy of future residents and in accordance with policy H13 of the Unitary Development Plan.

Details of the 'green roof' to be installed above the two storey wing of the lifelong learning centre and the 'brown roof' to be installed on the roof of the garden housing together with maintenance schedules shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority and thereafter implemented prior to the occupation of the respective part of the building on which the green or brown roof is located.Reason: In the interests of biodiversity and in accordance with policy G46 of the Unitary Development Plan.

A scheme showing the provisions to be made for CCTV camera coverage shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. The approved scheme shall be implemented prior to occupation of the building and shall be retained unless otherwise agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority.Reason: In the interests of enhancing security and safety and in accordance with policy DE6 of the Unitary Development Plan.

A scheme showing the provisions to be made for external lighting shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. The approved scheme shall be implemented prior to occupation of the building and shall be retained unless otherwise agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority.Reason: In the interests of enhancing security and safety and in accordance with policy DE6 of the Unitary Development Plan.

Details of the measures to be undertaken for the protection of the building from vehicle movements within the service yard shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. The approved scheme shall be implemented prior to occupation of the building and shall be retained unless otherwise agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority.Reason: In order to protect the building from damage from vehicle movements and in accordance with policy T32 of the Unitary Development Plan.

The development shall not commence until details of the measures to be taken to protect blind and partially sighted people from the V shaped support columns on the north-western side of the building have been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority.Reason: In the interests of health and safety and in accordance with policy C.15 of the Unitary Development Plan.

All 37 flats on the 7th floor of the development hereby approved shall be served by solar hot water heating panels in accordance with details to be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. None of the 7th floor flats shall be occupied until the approved system has been installed. Reason:In the interests of promoting renewable energy in accordance with policy G40 of the Unitary Development Plan and policy 4A.9 of the London Plan.

No approval is hereby given to the details submitted within Section 7 'Landscape Report' of the revised reserved matters submission statement dated 3 March 2006. Detailed landscape drawings including a landscape management strategy for the residential courtyard area shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. The approved scheme shall be implemented in the first planting and seeding seasons following the occupation of the first residential unit or completion of the development, whichever is the sooner unless the Local Planning Authority agree to any revised timescale in writing. Any trees or plants which within a period of 5 years from the completion of the development die, are removed or become seriously damaged or diseased, shall be replaced in the next planting season with others of similar size and species unless the Local Planning Authority gives written consent to any variation.Reason: To safeguard and improve the appearance of the area in accordance with policy H13 of the Unitary Development Plan and in order to comply with Section 197 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990.

The lifelong learning centre shall not be occupied until detailed landscape drawings including a landscape management strategy for the 'BLLC garden' have been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. The approved scheme shall be carried out in the first planting and seeding seasons following the occupation of the lifelong learning centre or completion of the development, whichever is the sooner unless the Local Planning Authority agree to any revised timescale in writing. Any trees or plants which within a period of 5 years from the completion of the development die, are removed or become seriously damaged or diseased, shall be replaced in the next planting season with others of similar size and species unless the Local Planning Authority gives written consent to any variation.Reason: To safeguard and improve the appearance of the area in accordance with policy H13 of the Unitary Development Plan and in order to comply with Section 197 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990.

A scheme showing detailed landscape drawings for the area beneath the arcade on the north western elevation of the building and to the Town Hall Square shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. The approved scheme shall be implemented prior to the first occupation of the building unless the Local Planning Authority agree to any revised timescale in writing.Reason: To ensure that the development is satisfactorily landscaped in order to improve the visual amenity of the area in accordance with policy DE16 of the Unitary Development Plan.
borough: London Borough of Barking and Dagenham
